\begin{aligned} &(-1, 10) \implies t = -1 + 10 = 9, \\ &(1, -10) \implies t = 1 - 10 = -9, \\ &(-2, 5) \implies t = -2 + 5 = 3, \\ &(2, -5) \implies t = 2 - 5 = -3, \\ &(-5, 2) \implies t = -5 + 2 = -3, \\ &(5, -2) \implies t = 5 - 2 = 3, \\ &(-10, 1) \implies t = -10 + 1 = -9, \\ &(10, -1) \implies t = 10 - 1 = 9. \end{aligned}
\] The possible values of \(t\) are \(9, -9, 3, -3\). The product of these values is \((9)(-9)(3)(-3) = 729\). Therefore, the product of all constants \(t\) is \(\boxed{729}\). </think> <answer> 729 </answer>
